Economy of Italy


Milan is the financial centre of Italy



Currency
Euro (EUR), except in Campione d'Italia (CHF)



Fiscal year

calendar year



Trade organisations

European Union, WTO, OECD, AIIB


Statistics


GDP
$1.850,735 trillion (nominal, 2016); $2.234,500 trillion (PPP, 2016)[1]


GDP rank
8th (nominal) / 12th (PPP)



GDP growth

 +0.4% Q1 2017,+1.2% acquired 2017 [2]



GDP per capita

$30,507 (nominal, 2016);
$36,833 (PPP, 2016)



GDP by sector

services (74%), industry (24%), agriculture (2%)



Inflation (CPI)

 +1.2% (June 2017)



Population below poverty line

5.7% in poverty, 2014;[3] 24.7% at risk of poverty or social exclusion, 2014[4]



Gini coefficient

0.324 (2015)[5]



Labour force

 25.7 million



Labour force by occupation

services (68%), industry (28%), agriculture (4%)


Unemployment
 11.1% May 2017



Average gross salary


€20,690 ($23,260), yearly (+1.3%) (2016)
[6] (as gross income and not gross wage)



Main industries

iron and steel, cement, chemicals, plastics, production machinery, motor vehicles, shipbuilding, space and aircraft, machine tools, communications, medical apparatus, pharmaceuticals, food and beverages processing, textiles, clothing, fashion, home appliances, tourism



Ease-of-doing-business rank

50th (2017)[7]


External


Exports
 $436.3 billion (2016)[8]



Export goods

engineering products; electrical equipment; vehicles, aircraft and vessels; base metals and steel; textiles, clothing and footwear; chemicals; food and beverages; precious metals; optical and medical apparatus; stone, cement and glass products; paper



Main export partners

 Germany 12.6%
 France 11.1%
 United States 6.8%
  Switzerland 5.7%
 United Kingdom 4.7%
 Spain 4.4%


Imports
 $372.2 billion (2016)[9]



Import goods

minerals; engineering products; chemicals; motor vehicles; base metals; plastics; textiles



Main import partners

 Germany 14.7%
 France 8.4%
 China 8.4%
 Russia 6.3%
 Netherlands 5.8%
 Spain 4.5%



FDI stock

$0.7 trillion



Gross external debt

 $2.6 trillion


Public finances



Public debt

 131% of GDP


Revenues
$1.0 trillion


Expenses
$1.1 trillion


